--------------------Assignment 3----------------------

-------------------Commands---------------------------
1.ls - Display hidden files 

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ ls -a
->.  ..  22.txt  23.txt  three

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2.rename - Rename all *.txt files to *.htm

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ rename 's/\.txt$/\.htm/' *.txt

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3.ln -s - Create symbolic link (shortcut) for a file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ ln -s niku

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4.ln - Create hard link for a file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ ln 22.htm sai

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5.stat - Display time stamp of the file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ stat sai
  File: sai
  Size: 0         	Blocks: 0          IO Block: 4096   regular empty file
Device: 803h/2051d	Inode: 4473005     Links: 2
Access: (0664/-rw-rw-r--)  Uid: ( 1000/ sunbeam)   Gid: ( 1000/ sunbeam)
Access: 2024-06-01 18:01:38.778052971 +0530
Modify: 2024-06-01 18:01:38.778052971 +0530
Change: 2024-06-01 18:54:18.371129355 +0530
 Birth: 2024-06-01 18:01:38.778052971 +0530

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

6.touch - Change the time stamp of the file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ touch sai

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

7.touch - Create empty file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ touch neeraj

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

8.tail - Print all lines in a file from fifth line onwards

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ tail -2 22.htm

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9.init 0, poweroff - Shutdown (Only for super-user)


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

10.init 6, reboot - Reboot (Only for super-user)


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

12.whoami - Find current user

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ whoami
->sunbeam

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

13.tty - Find current terminal

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop/one/two$ tty
->/dev/pts/0

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
14.who am i - Find current user and terminal

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~$ whoami
->sunbeam

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

15.users - Find all users logged into the system

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~$ users
->sunbeam

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

16.who - Find all users logged in and terminals in use

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~$ who
->sunbeam  tty2         2024-05-31 22:27 (tty2)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

17.grep, egrep, fgrep - Find a given word/pattern from the file

->

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


18.chmod - Make a file as read-only

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop$ chmod g=r myName.txt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

19.chmod - Make a file as write, read and execute

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop$ chmod g=rwx myName.txt

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

20.wc (using redirection) - Take input from the file, count words and store output to other file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop$ wc myName.txt > WordCount.txt 
->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop$ cat WordCount.txt 
-> 2 11 57 myName.txt 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


21.who | wc (using pipe) - Count words in output of “who” command

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop$ who | wc
->      1       5      46

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

22.head, tail (using pipe) - Print lines 5 to 10 from the given file

->sunbeam@sunbeam-HP-15-TS-Notebook-PC:~/Desktop$ head -10 PipeDemo.txt | tail -6
5
6
7
8
9
10

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


